{{Infobox lake | name = Volgograd Reservoir | image = Utes step raz1.jpg | caption = [[Stepan Razin Cliff]] | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = | coords = {{coord|49.13|N|44.94|E|region:RU_type:waterbody_source:dewiki|display=inline,title}} | type = [[reservoir]] | inflow = [[Volga River]] | outflow = [[Volga River]] | catchment = | basin_countries = Russia | length = {{convert|540|km|abbr=on}} | width = {{convert|17|km|abbr=on}} | area = {{convert|3117|km2|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = | volume = {{convert|31.5|km3|acre.ft|abbr=on}} | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | frozen = | islands = | sections = | cities = [[Kamyshin]] }} The '''Volgograd Reservoir''' ({{lang-ru|Волгоградское водохранилище}}) is a [[reservoir]] in [[Russia]] formed at the [[Volga River]] by the dam of the [[Volga Hydroelectric Station]]. It lies within the [[Volgograd Oblast]] and [[Saratov Oblast]] and named after the city of [[Volgograd]]. It was constructed during 1958-1961.
Its area is 3,117&nbsp;km², volume is 31,5&nbsp;km³, length is 540&nbsp;km, maximal width is 17&nbsp;km, average depth is 10.1 m. It is the third largest reservoir on [[Volga]] in Russia (after [[Kuybyshev Reservoir]] and [[Rybinsk Reservoir]]).
